<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-14T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/339: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Puerto Cortés</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WTC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wasson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortés</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-14T08:00:00-06:00">November
                                    14, 1932—8 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Government forces captured San Pedro Sula early this morning. <persName corresp="#p_CWE1">Coleman</persName> reported killed in plaza. Am
                            informed that no foreigners were killed or wounded.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WTC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wasson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>